Phase 3: Context Service Changes (External Dependency)
Background: Existing Inventory API Infrastructure

The current sitecore.ep.proxy.oc worker demonstrates a proven pattern for OrderCloud tenant discovery:
Sitecore Tenant ID → Inventory API → OrderCloud Configuration

Inventory API Response (from GET /api/inventory/v1/tenants/{tenantId}):
{
  id: string;                           // Sitecore tenant ID
  annotations: {
    URL: string;                        // OrderCloud API base URL (e.g., "https://api.ordercloud.io")
    MarketplaceId: string;              // OrderCloud Marketplace ID
  };
  labels: {
    Region: string;                     // e.g., "usw", "eu-west"
    Environment: string;                // "sandbox", "staging", "production"
    'OrderCloud.ApiInstance': string;   // API instance identifier
    'OrderCloud.MarketplaceType': string;
  };
}

This means region, environment, base_url, and marketplace_id are already discoverable via the tenant ID alone. The key question is how to handle the SitecoreAI OrderCloud Client ID for buyer authentication.
Decision: SitecoreAI OrderCloud Client ID Configuration
Option A: Explicit Provisioning (Recommended)

Store the sitecoreai_client_id in the Inventory API tenant annotations during SitecoreAI tenant provisioning.

Rationale:

    The SitecoreAI OrderCloud Client ID has specific requirements:

        Anonymous access enabled

        "Allow All Buyers" access scope

        Specific allowed grant types (client_credentials, password)

    These requirements are best validated and enforced at provisioning time

    Avoids runtime OC API calls for client discovery/creation

    Provisioning system has the elevated credentials needed to create API clients

Inventory API Schema Addition (annotations):
annotations: {
  URL: string;
  MarketplaceId: string;
  'SitecoreAI.ClientId': string;        // NEW: SitecoreAI OrderCloud Client ID
  'SitecoreAI.ClientSecret'?: string;   // Optional: For server-to-server flows if needed later
}

Provisioning Workflow:

    SitecoreAI tenant provisioning creates or links an OrderCloud marketplace

    Provisioning creates a dedicated API Client in OrderCloud with:

        AllowAnyBuyer: true

        IsAnonBuyer: true

        AccessTokenDuration: 600 (or configurable)

        AllowedCorsDomains: ['*'] (or restricted to known domains)

    Provisioning updates Inventory API with SitecoreAI.ClientId annotation

    Client ID is available to the storefront proxy via existing Inventory API call

Option B: Dynamic Discovery (Alternative)

Store only the OrderCloud tenant ID; system authenticates to OC API at runtime to discover or create the SitecoreAI Client ID.

Pros:

    Minimal initial configuration

    Self-healing if client is deleted

Cons:

    Requires proxy to have elevated OC credentials

    First request latency for client discovery

    "Auto-create" concern: Should a proxy create API clients? (User note: hesitant on this)

    Discovery requires listing all API clients and filtering by naming convention

