Decisions

    New worker vs extending existing: New sitecore.ep.proxy.storefront worker for clean separation of auth logic and independent deployment

    Context required: Storefront routes require Context ID (unlike current /oc/* which allows no context)

    Token ownership: Client manages OC tokens; proxy validates format, OC validates authenticity

    Endpoint allowlist: Strict buyer-only endpoints; admin endpoints blocked at proxy

    OrderCloud resource type: Minimal context resource with just tenant_id; other config derived from Inventory API

    SitecoreAI OrderCloud Client ID: Created during tenant provisioning, stored as SitecoreAI.ClientId annotation in Inventory API (Option A). Rationale:

        Provisioning has the elevated credentials to create OC API Clients

        Validates client requirements (anonymous access, allow all buyers) at setup time

        Avoids proxy needing OC admin credentials or auto-creation logic

        Consistent with existing Inventory API pattern for tenant configuration

    No auto-create for Client ID: If SitecoreAI.ClientId is missing, return 503 rather than attempting to create one dynamically

Further Considerations

    Anonymous buyer session initialization — Should the proxy auto-obtain an anonymous token if none provided (using stored Buyer Client ID)? Recommendation: No, keep client responsible for token lifecycle to maintain session state (cart persistence).

    Rate limiting — Should storefront proxy implement its own rate limiting, or rely on OrderCloud? Recommendation: Start with OC limits; add Cloudflare rate limiting later if needed for DDoS protection.

    Caching — Should product catalog responses be cached at the proxy level? Recommendation: Defer to v2; start with passthrough only.

    Migration for existing OrderCloud tenants — Existing tenants in the Inventory API won't have the SitecoreAI.ClientId annotation. Options:

        Manual migration: Platform team runs script to create OC clients and update annotations

        Portal self-service: Add UI in Platform Portal for customers to trigger client creation

        Graceful degradation: If annotation missing, proxy returns 503 with actionable error message pointing to setup docs

    Recommendation: Graceful degradation initially; add Portal self-service for GA.

    SitecoreAI Client ID naming convention — Use consistent naming for discoverability and potential future tooling:

        Pattern: SitecoreAI-Storefront-{marketplaceId}

        Allows admin scripts to identify SitecoreAI-managed clients

    Multi-storefront scenarios — A single OrderCloud marketplace might power multiple storefronts (e.g., B2C and B2B sites). Options:

        One SitecoreAI Client per marketplace (shared across storefronts)

        Multiple SitecoreAI Clients per marketplace (one per Context)

    Recommendation: Start with one client per marketplace; evaluate multi-client if distinct buyer pools needed.